ALGONQUIN WINDSOR LOCKS LLC FERC ELECTRIC TARIFF
1. Availability: Algonquin Windsor Locks LLC ("Seller") makes electric energy and capacity available under this FERC Electric Tariff, Original Volume No. 1 ("Tariff') to any purchaser for resale.
2. Applicability: This Tariff is applicable to all sales by Seller of energy, capacity and the ancillary services described below, to the extent such sales are subject to the jurisdiction of the Commission, to eligible purchasers that are not otherwise subject to a particular tariff or rate schedule on file with the Commission.
3. Ancillary Services: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service (automatic generator control), operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service) to purchasers within the markets administered by the ISO New England, Inc.
4. Rates: All sales made under this Tariff shall be made at rates negotiated between the Seller and purchaser.
5. Other Terms and Conditions: All other terms and conditions for sales under this Tariff shall be established by agreement between the Seller and purchaser.
6. Compliance with Commission Regulations: Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this Tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the Seller's market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 CFR Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller's market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Tariff.
7. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market-Based Rate Authority: Seller has been granted the following waivers and blanket authorization in Docket No. ER10-716- 000: (a) waiver of the provisions of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission's regulations, regarding the filing of rate schedules, except sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15, and 35.16; (b) waiver of accounting and other requirements in Parts 41, 101, and 141 of the Commission's regulations; and (c) blanket authorization under Section 204 of the Federal Power Act and Part 34 of the Commission's regulations for all future issuances of securities or assumptions of liabilities. Sales made by Seller under the Amended and Restated Electricity Purchase Agreement, dated December 1, 1987, by and between The Connecticut Light and Power Company and Seller with regard to the energy and output of a qualifying cogeneration facility owned by Seller are exempt from Section 205 of the Federal Power Act. The cogeneration facility was self-recertified as a qualifying facility in Docket No. QF86-765-002. See Ahlstrom Windsor Locks Cogeneration LLC, Docket No. QF86-765-002, Notice of Self-Recertification as a Qualifying Cogeneration Facility (August 17, 2000).
8. Revisions to Tariff: Seller may file revisions to this Tariff with the Commission. Nothing contained in this Tariff shall be construed as affecting or limiting in any way the right of Seller to unilaterally file with the Commission for a change in any aspect of this Tariff under Section 205 of the Federal Power Act pursuant to the Commission's Rules and Regulations.
9. Seller Category:
Seller is a Category 2 seller in the Northeast Region, as defined in C.F.R. 35.36(a).
Seller is a Category 1 seller in all other regions, as defined in 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a).
10. Effective Date: This Tariff shall become effective on the date specified by the Commission.
